<left>
Using curly braces around parameters provides many benefits
including:

Appending letters to the content of variables: <green>"${ANIMAL}s"<clear>
Multi-digit positional parameters: <green>"${23}"<clear>
Calling from arrays by index or key: <green>"${ARRAY[42]}"<clear> or <green>"${ARRAY[Color]}"<clear>
Finding the length of the contents: <green>"${#PASSWD}"<clear> or <green>"${#DWARVES[@]}"<clear>
Converting the case of the contents: <green>"${NAME^}"<clear> and <green>"${FILE,,}"<clear>
Removing substrings: <green>"${FULLNAME## }"<clear> or <green>"${FULLNAME%% }"<clear>
Replacing substrings: <green>"${WAR_DECREE/Eurasia/Eastasia}"<clear>
Extracting substrings by location: <green>"${PHONE_NUM:1:3}"<clear>
Setting default values: <green>"${SHELL:-/bin/bash}"<clear> or <green>"${SHELL:=/bin/bash}"<clear>
</left>
